# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Names of the infra / third-party secrets Harmonic expects — REFERENCE ONLY.
#
# This is a contract, not a store. Harmonic is open source and deployed by many
# operators, so NO secret material — plaintext or ciphertext — ever lives in
# this repo. Each value is bring-your-own and stays private to your deployment.
#
# To supply them, materialize one file per name below under $SECRETS_DIR
# (default `secrets/run/`, gitignored), which the compose `secrets:` overlay
# mounts to /run/secrets/<NAME>. Two supported ways:
#
#   1. Pre-place the files yourself (scp, config-mgmt, your password manager's
#      CLI). This is the default; scripts/deploy.sh needs no hook.
#   2. Install a populate hook that fetches from your private source at deploy
#      time. See secrets/adapters/ for example hooks (SOPS+age, AWS SSM, Vault).
#
# SCOPE: infra + third-party secrets only. App-internal secrets
# (SECRET_KEY_BASE, AGENT_RUNNER_SECRET) belong in Rails encrypted credentials
# (config/credentials.yml.enc) — different owner, blast radius, and rotation
# cadence. See docs/INFRASTRUCTURE.md.
#
# One file per NAME; the file's contents are the value. Names (no values):
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Database connection string          (from `terraform output -raw database_url`)
DATABASE_URL

# Redis password                      (generate: openssl rand -hex 24)
REDIS_PASSWORD

# DigitalOcean Spaces (ActiveStorage) — from terraform outputs
DO_SPACES_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY

# AWS SES SMTP credential             (minted from an IAM user; NOT via terraform)
SMTP_PASSWORD

# Stripe (billing + AI gateway)
STRIPE_API_KEY
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET

# OAuth
GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET

# Agent-runner shared secret
AGENT_RUNNER_SECRET

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Non-secret settings (Spaces region/bucket/endpoint, SMTP username, Stripe
# publishable/gateway keys, Sentry DSN, etc.) are plain configuration and stay
# in the environment / compose config, not here.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
